  "texts": [
    "Therefore, accountability and the need to establish legitimacy is more important for the public sector (whether it develops AI systems on its own or through public-private partnerships, as long as the deployment is in the public sector) than it is for the private sector.",
    "Still, even if the normative obligations that attach to power are less applicable to companies there is good reason to think that transparency should be understood along similar lines.",
    "When companies have to show to regulators that their decision-making processes are legitimate, the same considerations of outcome-and process-based factors will be relevant.",
    "Likewise, if companies want to convince their clients that they are using AI in an acceptable manner the way in which to show this will be the same.",
    "The difference is, rather, one of degree: companies might have a lower bar to meet before the use of an AI system is legitimate (because it's not using public funds and because it typically has less power over citizens)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}